Setup Raspberry Pi
Enable Bluetooth: Ensure Bluetooth is enabled on your Raspberry Pi.

Install Bluetooth Packages:

sh
Copy code
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install bluetooth bluez python-bluez
Pair the Raspberry Pi with the Android Device:

On the Raspberry Pi, use the following commands to pair:
sh
Copy code
bluetoothctl
agent on
scan on
On the Android device, go to Bluetooth settings and pair with the Raspberry Pi when it appears.
